INFO-I210 - Information Infrastructure I

The learning objectives of this course include the following:
1.  To familiarize students with some of the basic programming skills. 
2. To familiarize students with basic programming tools for solving computational problems in biomedical informatics.
3. Install and configure software needed for developing Python scripts.
4. Program in Python using variables, constants, data, conditional statements, and loops.
5.  Collect and process user input.
6.  Modularize complex programs with functions and file inclusion.
7. Construct and use arrays in Python.
8. Manipulate strings in Python.
9. Visualize data using Python.
